raw_data.title: Collection Specialist
raw_data.description: Safeguards customer funds via the timely and accurate recovery of overpaid or erroneously paid invoices. Recovers funds through various mechanisms including, but not limited to, refund, offset of invoice payments, creating extended repayment schedules, and negotiations with appropriate entities via telephone and written communication. Validates overpayment by reviewing cases to determine if overpayment was assessed correctly. Investigates cases to determine responsible entities and contacts responsible parties such as vendors, attorneys, consultants, or other designated representative to advise them of the liability and responsibility for debt, request documentation, and to discuss overpayment options. Educates the responsible party on roles and responsibilities for collection of the overpayment and the documentation requirements for requesting a review and or appeal. Understands basic accounting principles in order to interpret and analyze various financial documents, problem solve, research, and communicate effectively. Possesses a working knowledge of personal computer software applications. Negotiates with responsible party to determine the overpayment option that meets the responsible party’s needs, are within the agency’s guidelines, and/or are approved by the appropriate agency representatives. Implements the recovery of debt from other Federal Agencies for responsible party who refuses to pay back monies.
